# Frontend Rules

## Design Skill

ALWAYS read and follow the frontend-design skill at `.cursor/skills/frontend-design/SKILL.md` before writing any frontend code. The project aims for a super polished, cute, welcoming aesthetic -- inspired by Balatro's vibe. Every UI element should feel intentional and delightful.

## MCP Tools

- **shadcn MCP**: Search and add components from the shadcn registry. Check what's available before building custom components.
- **Next.js DevTools MCP**: Use for debugging, performance insights, and route inspection.
- **Vercel Plugin**: Follow React/Next.js best practices from Vercel engineering.
- **Context7**: Look up Next.js, React, Tailwind, and Motion docs when needed.

## Component Patterns

- Use React Server Components by default. Add `"use client"` only when the component needs interactivity, hooks, or browser APIs.
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for all Tailwind class merging.
- Prefer shadcn/ui components from `@/components/ui/` over custom implementations.
- Use the Motion library (already installed as `motion`) for animations.
- Components go in `components/` (shared) or co-located in `app/` route directories (page-specific).
- Hooks go in `hooks/`.

## Styling

- Use Tailwind CSS v4 utility classes.
- Use CSS variables defined in `app/globals.css` for theming (shadcn tokens).
- Dark mode is supported via the `.dark` class.

## Testing

- React components must be tested using `@testing-library/react` with `happy-dom`.
- Test user interactions and rendered output, not implementation details.
- Tests live in `__tests__/` directories adjacent to the components.

## Data Fetching

- Use Convex hooks (`useQuery`, `useMutation`, `useAction`) from `convex/react` for all data.
- The `ConvexClientProvider` wraps the app in `app/layout.tsx`.
- Prefer reactive queries (`useQuery`) over one-shot fetches for real-time data.
